    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Considerations for Product Searchability\n Controlling Search, Facet, and Display Behavior for Fields\n Mark Products as Searchable or Not Searchable\n Mark Product Fields as Searchable\n Add Product Search Filters (Facets)\n Configure How to Display Search Results\n Sort Options\n Commerce Search Index\n Manage No Search Results\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nAdd Product Search Filters (Facets)\n\nFilters—also called facets—enable buyers and shoppers to narrow their search results. You can create filters from product fields, such as size, finish, and color. A filter can also include selectable values. For example, a color filter can have the values red, blue, and green. If a filter has values, they appear on the results page under the parent filter.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience and Salesforce mobile app\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\n\nWhen adding product filters, keep these considerations in mind.\n\nSearch can use up to 50 product fields as possible filters.\nCategory is the only default field. It’s always included as a filter option, and you can't remove it. You can select up to 49 other fields.\nCommerce Search limits the number of searchable values that you can configure. You can configure individual maximums of 25 searchable fields, 50 results filters, and 10 sortable fields but only up to a combined maximum of 70 values. For example, you can configure 20 searchable fields, 40 results filters, and 10 sortable fields, or any combination totaling 70.\nThe use of HTML rich-text is not supported when creating picklist values.\nField-level security settings aren’t applied to filters. Only add filters that you want shoppers to use.\n\nSearch shows up to 10 facets for search results. By default, these facets include the Category field and the first nine fields in the order that they appear in the Selected Fields column. However, if you choose to automatically select the 10 most-relevant facets, the order in the Selected Fields column is ignored. Instead, based on their relevance to the search results, nine fields are selected from the Selected Fields column and used as facets along with Category.\n\nNOTE Make sure to rebuild the index after adding or removing fields in the Selected Fields column.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Search.\nOn the Results Filters tab, click Manage Filters.\nIn the Available Fields column, move up to 49 filters to the Selected Fields column.\nTo change the display order of the filters, select a filter in the right column and use the up and down arrows to move the filter.\nIf you choose to automatically select the 10 most-relevant facets, the order in the Selected Fields column is ignored.\nSave your changes, and on the Search Index Summary tab, rebuild the index.\nIMPORTANT For B2B stores, we recommend that you localize all filter values, such as red, blue, and green on a color filter. By localizing the values, you ensure that all filters appear as expected. For more information about translation and localization, see Sell Globally.\nSEE ALSO\nMark Products as Searchable or Not Searchable\nMark Product Fields as Searchable\nConfigure How to Display Search Results\nAutomatically Select the Most Relevant Facets\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
